I tell ya, it sucks being a Blizzard fan boi
In general, Blizzard is WAAAAAAAAAAAAAY too slow when it comes to any kind of major changes.  Meaning something in the game may be stupidly over(or under)powered for months
Or they overreact and something goes from being viable if slightly overpowered to nonviable

Basically, I think they tune their game from a statistics / data analysis standpoint, so they implement something, let data build, analyze it, then implement changes.  But they only implement those changes when new stuff is about to be added
So unpredictable results can occur.  Essentially, they do a shitty job of being game *designers* :P
My job, is a Youtuber and I get shit, Views
That's a problem with most online games though. Something is strong, then instead of just nerfing 1 thing to see if that helps that nerf 5 different things and it becomes complete shit
or you do the World of Warships things and when there's a russian ship with OP armor you nerf it's already useless Anti Air so you can claim you nerfed it :ptv-confused:
Currently I'm playing an enhancement shaman
But in 8.1, they utterly destroyed the class' pvp potential
They nerfed damage, healing, and our mana pool (smart move blizzard, make us heal less AND give us less casts...)
Why?  The "turbo" comp in arena was a smidge too strong
So obviously the answer was to make us hit like a wet noodle and make us squishy like marshmallow at the same time
Couldn't have done one or the other, just HAD to do everything and be an overachiever :P
In all seriousness though, Blizzard is special, because they can break something and then leave it broken for 6 - 12 months.  It's not good.

The first person I killed was actually a T27
Fully upgraded, 1,250 health.  I two-shot him.

Came in fast down a hill, trying to get close to me.  But heavy tanks don't do turning too well, especially when over their top rated speed going down hill.  I put a well-placed shot into his side just behind the turret and lit them on fire
They didn't have a fire extinguisher either, so that fire burnt for the full duration.  My 2nd shot just needed to love-tap them.
From there, I more or less destroyed tier 5 - 6 tanks that were there to back him up
At the very end of the game, I ran out of my premium HEAT rounds, and had to use HE.  I killed an IS-2 by shooting its ass with those rounds xD
